description: Feelgood Svenska AB engages in the provision of healthcare services. The company is headquartered in Stockholm, Stockholm and currently employs 542 full-time employees.  The firm operates within two business areas, namely Business, which offers medical services directed to the corporate market, and Private, which offers training and physiotherapy to private customers. As of December 31, 2011, Feelgood Svenska AB was operational in Sweden through its wholly owned subsidiaries, such as directly owned Haluxa AB, as well as hte indirectly held: Feelgood Foretagshalsovard AB, Feelgood Sjukvard AB, Hagabadet AB, Feelgood Vitea AB and Feelgood Primarvard AB. As of December 31, 2011, the Company’s three biggest shareholders were Provobis Holding Aktiebolag (22.1%), Hepatica Invest Aktiebolag (12.4%) and Ringvagen Venture AB (10.8%). On July 9, 2012, the Company announced the completion of the sale of its training facilities in Linkoping, Vasteras, Skovde and Motala.
name: Feelgood Svenska AB (publ)
